file=Brand Studio/spark/operational/skill/spark-skill-routing.md · h=name: spark-skill-routing\ntype: operational/skill\nstatus: consolidated from the "Boundaries" sections of spark's skill files — no new logic invented\nassigned_agent: spark (Brand Studio / Creative Director — department leader)\ndate_added: 2026-07-07\n · p:=Spark's routing map. Triggers: `operational/commands/spark-commands.md`.\n · wif:Where Identity Fits=Spark is Brand Studio's leader and carries the active identity (`identity/idea-guardian-david-ogilvy.md`). Identity governs delivery — candid, cited, fix-always-attached; it never changes a threshold, checklist, or verdict. Universal principles win over persona.\n · cag:Coach and Gate (the two-skill split)=```\nart-direction-critique   (COACH — advisory, upstream, 5-axis scored: · tb=\|                   concept/craft/composition/coherence/finishing → · tb=\|                   SHIP / REWORK / KILL with prioritized concrete fixes) · cag:Coach and Gate (the two-skill split)=v\ncoherence-qa             (GATE — binary, cited, blocking:\natlas kit ✓ \· lena voice ✓ \· weave arc ✓ \· bleed ✓ \·\n[behavioral — dormant] \· coherence judgment →\nPASS ships / FIX LIST returns)\n```\n\nWork should meet the coach before it meets the gate; the gate is not a place to discover concept problems.\n · hr:Handoff Rules=- **All outbound creative → coherence-qa.** Pixel's batches, pulse's posts/series, lena's campaigns/sequences, rio's ad creatives — no exemptions, no partial ships.\n- **Gate consumes lane results**: atlas audits, lena voice checks + humanic confirmations, weave arc verdicts + ledger refs; missing lanes get run, never waived. Lanes own their lanes; spark owns the whole.\n- **Drift and BLEED converge here**: atlas's repeat-violation notes and multi-brand BLEED findings, weave's ARC GAPs, repeat fix-list patterns — spark judges evolution-vs-error and routes amendment questions to the operator. Spark never amends the documents itself.\n- **Operator overrides of the gate** are logged like board overrules (precedent's discipline); repeated overrides mean law or gate needs amending.\n- **muse → spark** (per catalog): top campaign concepts get a coherence sanity check (coach mode) before development.\n- **Cross-department:** board gates decisions, spark gates creative — an ad campaign's spend clears board, its creative clears spark. Behavioral review slots between lena's wording and this gate when that department exists. Echo's investor materials are echo's own lane (marcus/board supervise), but brand-visual elements echo uses still meet atlas's kit.\n · p:Precedence=Submitted-for-ship → gate. "Thoughts on this / make it better" → coach. Both → coach first. Ambiguous → ask which is wanted; the answer changes spark's authority (advice vs block).\n · f:=No written law in a lane (kit/guide/arc missing) → the gate's power narrows to recommend-only for that lane, stated plainly — and the definer's creation loop is the real fix.\n